Hello I’m Cathy a Designer, Developer and Blogger from Cheshire.

I have over 10 years industry experience and am passionate about User Experience, Interaction Design, Service Design, Accessibility, Web Standards, Web Performance, and Responsive Development. I work with CSS (including Sass and PostCSS), HTML and JavaScript as well as a sketch pad, some post-it notes and my favourite pen.

I have experience across all sectors of the digital industry including, Interaction Design, UX Design, UI Design, Prototyping, User Testing, and Front End Development.

Over the years I have been fortunate enough to work on a number of exciting digital projects for well-known companies and agencies including…

  • Defra
  • Environment Agency
  • Barclays
  • Nintendo
  • Sainsbury’s
  • EE
  • AO.com
  • Tropic Skincare
  • GetTheLabel.com
  • My Protein
  • Elizabeth Arden
  • Zavvi

As well as the articles on this site I have also written articles for Sitepoint , Blog posts on Medium and Tutorials for Mr Frontend.

Examples of my code can be found in my Github open source projects or in Codepen demonstrations.
